groovy.lang

Class Sequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList
          • groovy.lang.Sequence
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GroovyObject, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable, Collection, List, RandomAccess
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NonEmptySequence

    public class Sequence
extends ArrayList
implements GroovyObject
    Represents a sequence of objects which represents zero or many instances of of objects of a given type. The type can be omitted in which case any type of object can be added.
    Author:
    James Strachan
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
